type: web_research
title: Dual Investment Options Theory & Mathematical Models Research
key_insights[10]: "Black-Scholes model applies to crypto with q=0 (no dividends), T=days/365 (24/7 trading), and higher IV (40-120% vs stocks 15-30%)",Bitcoin options exhibit FORWARD SKEW (commodity-class) not reverse skew (equity-class) - OTM calls have higher IV than OTM puts,Newton-Raphson method converges in 3-5 iterations for IV calculation; Bisection as fallback (18-39 iterations),Deribit holds ~90% of crypto options market share - primary IV data source via public API,"Theta decay accelerates non-linearly: 7→0 DTE captures ~40% of remaining time value","Optimal DI period: 3-7 day short-term rotation maximizes Theta efficiency","Kelly Criterion: Half Kelly recommended (75% of optimal growth, 50% less drawdown)","HMM regime detection: 2-state model (low-vol=DI optimal, high-vol=DI cautious) reduces max drawdown from 35.7% to 24%","Wheel strategy Sharpe ratio: 1.083 vs SPY buy-and-hold 0.70 (QuantConnect study)","In traditional markets, underlying position accounts for 94-99% of Wheel total return; crypto premium contribution is much higher due to 3-10x volatility"
refs[6]: dual_investment_research_report.md - Section 9 (Options Theory & Mathematical Models),"PMC 8418903 - Bitcoin IV estimation, forward skew, commodity classification",vollib.org - py_vollib for fast IV calculation (Peter Jäckel algorithm),"docs.deribit.com - API endpoints: get_instruments, get_order_book, get_historical_volatility",QuantConnect research/17871 - Wheel strategy backtest Sharpe 1.083,hmmlearn GaussianHMM - 2-state regime detection for crypto
recommendations[7]: Implement DeribitIVFetcher class for real-time IV data from Deribit API,Use py_vollib_vectorized for batch Greeks/IV calculation across option chains,Build HMM regime detector with hmmlearn to gate DI entries,Backtest Wheel strategy with historical BTC OHLCV data before live deployment,Use Half Kelly (0.5x) for position sizing in DI strategy,Combine Bollinger Bands (2σ) + S/R detection for optimal strike selection,Monte Carlo simulation with 100k paths for expected value validation before each DI entry
